result.execSummary:
All charges against Teresa A. Kennedy in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Teresa A. Kennedy is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:40 PM Defendant Teresa A. Kennedy appeared in court, Attorney Dennis G Brown appeared in court for Teresa A. Kennedy, Attorney  Mike Schiek appeared in court for State of Wisconsin. Calling 21CM34,  21CM72, 21Cm75, 21CM1 and 22CM17.  Court goes over record and notes an agreement reached and defendant to plead to all counts in cases 21CM72 and 21CM75 and State moves to dismiss remaining cases.  States motions to dismiss 21CM1, 21CM34 and 22CM17 are granted. Court questions Atty Brown as to how defendant pleads to 21CM72 and 21CM75/Atty Brown - No Contest.  Court questions defendant - enters a plea of No Contest. Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and accepts DEJ for 2 years. Bond continued and court notes cases set for review on February 6, 2023 at 3:00 p.m.  adj: 1:57p.m.

1:03 PM Defendant Teresa A. Kennedy not in court. Attorney Dennis G Brown appeared in court for Teresa A. Kennedy, DA Michael Schiek appears on behalf of ADA Jillian Pfeifer for the State of Wisconsin. Court statement. Brown did make contact with defendant earlier today. Brown made phone contact with defendant who indicates she is waiting for a cab; contact with cab was made around 12:20 p.m. Court speaks to counsel's availability later today, waits for defendant to show. 1:07 p.m. recess.

9:22 AM Defendant Teresa A. Kennedy not in court. Attorney Dennis G Brown appeared in court for Teresa A. Kennedy. Attorney Jillian Pfeifer appeared in court for State of Wisconsin. Calling 21CM1, 21CM34, 21CM72, 21CM75, 22CM17. Court reviews history of cases, agreement had been reached by counsel to resolve all cases. Defendant does not appear. Brown notes that he talked with defendant yesterday, but has had no contact with her this morning. Pfeifer requests warrant; granted. 9:24 a.m. adj.

3:22 PM Prosecuting attorney Jillian Pfeifer appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Teresa A. Kennedy appeared in court, Attorney Dennis G Brown appeared by video for Teresa A. Kennedy. Calling 21CM1, 21CM34, 21CM72, 21CM75 & 22CM17. 21CM34 is set for Jury Trial. Brown states Trial to remain. 22CM17 on calender for an adjourned initial appearance. Brown has not been appointed. Defendant has not contacted PD's office. Court directs Defendant to go to PD's office today. Court enters not guilty plea on case assuming Brown will be appointed. Court to set out. Bond continued. adj. 03:25 PM
Status conference scheduled for February 11, 2022 at 08:15 am.

1:28 PM Prosecuting attorney Jillian Pfeifer appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Teresa A. Kennedy appeared in court. Court review of case. Court questions Defendant on non-appearance. In receipt of complaint, right to counsel. Pfeifer statement to bail. $150 bond was posted. Court sets cash bond and quashes warrant adj.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for January 18, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
No abusive contact with C.G., A.L. & J.Y.

01:31 PM Prosecuting attorney Jillian Pfeifer appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Teresa Kennedy does not appear. Pfeifer states a citation was issued with todays date and time. Court authorizes warrant. adj. 01:32 PM
